trials.author: BNOC
info: Starting from this section we will look into
combos you'll want to learn from Day 1
before you get a good grasp at Old Joseph.
This one is a basic link from 2A into 236A,
your go-to meterless combo in STAND OFF.
An essential confirm at any skill level.
trials.name: Basics 01 - STAND OFF Basic Confirm

trials.author: BNOC
info: A jump-in variant of the previous trial.
You can add another 2A after the first one,
but for better consistency we use just one 2A.
Both J.B and J.C are your most decent jump-ins,
but J.C usually sees more use as an air-to-air.
An essential meterless confirm at any level.
trials.name: Basics 02 - STAND OFF Jumping Confirm

trials.author: BNOC
info: A simple dashing confirm into 236A/B.
Once again, an essential one to learn.
D.5B works as a mid to long range anti-air,
but D.2B is more consisent VS shorter chars.
trials.name: Basics 03 - STAND OFF Dashing Confirm

trials.author: BNOC
info: Meterless S.ON confirm into knockdown,
Can also be done with one S.5A, but two
S.5A's usually prove to be consistent enough.
The knockdown also lets you oki on characters
that have average to slow wakeup speeds.
trials.name: Basics 04 - STAND ON Basic Chain

trials.author: BNOC
info: Basic jump-in combo in STAND ON.
S.J.A has the most hitstun and best hitbox,
but S.J.C also works well enough to be used.
Likewise, gives you oki on specific characters.
trials.name: Basics 05 - STAND ON Jumping Confirm

trials.author: BNOC
info: A basic wrap confirm in STAND ON.
You can use any version of the wrap,
But personally i recommend the C version
since it's the easiest to combo into/off from.
Once again, you can get some oki after knockdown.
trials.name: Basics 06 - STAND ON Basic Wrap Confirm

trials.author: BNOC
info: Easy confirm against small characters, notably
being Stand OFF Iggy, crouching Devo and Alessi.
Sometimes you can confirm off 2A 2A, but using
just one 2A is advised for better consistency,
Gives you very simple oki afterwards.
trials.name: Basics 07 - STAND OFF Short Chars Basic Confirm

trials.author: BNOC
info: An easy and efficent way to spend meter.
Mashing during S.214A/B/C will let you do
more hits and damage.
Works on everyone except shorter characters.
trials.name: Basics 08 - STAND OFF Basic CC Confirm

trials.author: BNOC
trials.name: Basics 09 - STAND OFF Short Chars Basic CC
info: Another CC confirm, but this time
using a CC variant that hits short characters.
Once again, don't forget to mash during S.214.

trials.author: BNOC
info: Another CC confirm, but from S.ON.
You can confirm off one S.5A if you can.
Use S.2C>S.2B>S.2B>S.2B on short chars!
Remember to mash during S.214 too, boy.
trials.name: Basics 10 - STAND ON Basic CC Confirm

trials.author: BNOC
info: A basic command grab link from S.5A.
Since the command grab doesn't scale,
this link is important to learn for the
future combos on this trial list.
OJ's command grab also gives you oki which
we will look into in the next trials.
trials.name: Basics 11 - STAND ON Command Grab Link

trials.author: BNOC
info: Joseph's basic okizeme grab option.
It's recommended to use either the A or B
version of the command grab, since they
give the best frame advantage on wakeup and
work on midscreen as well. the C version is
only ever used to style on them as a round ender.
trials.name: Basics 12 - STAND OFF Basic Oki Scenario (Grab)

trials.author: BNOC
info: An extremely easy mix on okizeme.
This usually will give you enough frame
advantage to go for another mix, but it's
recommended to cancel into S.6248 for faster
recovery, then go on for another mixup.
OJ's mixups aren't amazing, so don't rely on it.
trials.name: Basics 13 - STAND OFF Basic Oki Scenario (Hit)

trials.author: BNOC
trials.name: Basics 14 - STAND ON Basic Oki Scenario (Grab)
info: A command grab mixup option in S.ON.
Unlike in S.OFF it's way easier to mix
them up since you are doing better damage
and have access to S.5A which can gives you
stronger frame advantage with the 360 link.

trials.author: BNOC
trials.name: Basics 15 - STAND ON Basic Oki Scenario (Hit)
info: The S.5A variant of S.ON oki which
lets you catch them jumping out of the
command grab okizeme option.
The trick to get it working is to not hit
S.5A on meaty, which can sometimes make it hard
against characters with fast pre-jump animations.

trials.author: BNOC
info: Basic Anti-Air combo if you have meter.
Good if you have spare meter or if it kills,
otherwise you should save it for CC confirms.
trials.name: Basics 16 - STAND ON Close Anti Air Combo

trials.author: BNOC
info: Another metered AA combo option.
Unlike the one before it, this one
gives you way more range and options.
The S.5C is a good way to catch lower jumps,
but if they are way higher it's recommended to
just use the S.214A right away and mash.
trials.name: Basics 17 - STAND ON Far Anti Air Combo

trials.author: BNOC
info: Optimal Day 2 CC Combo from Stand OFF.

so make sure you always have a bar.

recommended to learn if you don't like to

trials.author: BNOC
trials.name: Intermediate 05 - STAND ON 5A 3B 360 Link Practice
info: Let's see if you can handle what's to come.
Wocky link into command grab off S.3B, which
is the optimal damage route that we will use in
the Advanced section and in the next combo.

trials.author: BNOC
trials.name: Intermediate 06 - STAND OFF D.5B Confirm

trials.author: BNOC
trials.name: Advanced 01 - STAND OFF Optimal Full CC Combo
info: Finally we get to actually challenging combos.
This one is as optimal as you can get with 1 bar,
starting this one with S.OFF conversion from 2A.
Good luck :^)

trials.author: BNOC
trials.name: Advanced 02 - STAND ON Optimal Full CC Combo

Remember to cancel out of S.5AABC as soon
as you can for a consistent link.

trials.author: BNOC
trials.name: Advanced 03 - STAND CRASH Universal Combo
info: Universal Stand Crash combo.
Works on any character, it's not
as necessary to learn as you think, but
if you are going for optimal damage this
is the way to go about it.

techs back, but keep an eye on where they're 
going and not just mash out glass. 4A has a 
bit better of a hitbox usually, but 4B is 
better for contesting things like S. On

Super confirm

This sucks. Only use it as a finisher or if 
you're desperate for damage and/or have too 
much meter, the latter option not being common 
at all.

High risk, high reward. The super doesn't

grabbing instead of getting the raw 4C, plus

reaction.

This kills the opponent.

because it can't be safely linked into and 
will make you suck at the game if it's 
all you go for.

massive payout if you land it.
